How to Avail the Best Study Abroad Scholarships?

  • 471 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Mar 23,2023 01:56 PM IST

Deciding to study abroad can be expensive, but many study-abroad scholarships can assist students. Researching thoroughly and applying for multiple scholarships can increase the chances of receiving financial aid. The key is to be proactive in seeking out and applying for opportunities. Reading instructions and eligibility criteria are essential, and starting the search early can give students enough time to prepare a robust application. Connect with the Canam Consultants for valuable insights and support on study abroad scholarships.

  • • A Study Abroad Scholarship Matters
Read More


Choosing to study abroad is often perceived as expensive, but that is only sometimes true. Many study-abroad scholarships and grants help in procuring financial security. So, do not let the misconception of affordability hold you back from pursuing your study abroad dreams.
Some sacrifices are necessary to study abroad and keep a student financially secure. Students can realize their travel goals by adopting innovative saving tactics and leveraging financial aid opportunities, like study abroad scholarships. The key is to seek out and apply for these opportunities proactively.

Students are constantly worried about finances when deciding to study abroad. Do not worry, we have got our ten sure-fire steps to help students get the best study abroad scholarships!
However, we know our students' daily burdens, so we will not waste time with outdated ideas. Instead, we will cut straight to the chase and provide practical advice on winning those coveted scholarships.

Step 1 -  Seek Assistance

Students are always eager to explore the world and enrich their experience through study abroad programs. However, coping with the finances indeed creates a dilemma. Do not worry; plenty of resources are available to help students find scholarships and grants that can make their dreams of studying abroad come true.

What Should be the First Step?

First and foremost, do not hesitate to seek guidance from those around. Reach out to the university's study abroad office, professors, academic advisors, and financial aid office to inquire about any scholarships or grants they may be aware of. Visiting these offices in person is recommended, as this shows a student's dedication and initiative. It will make it easier for them to assist a student, and they will also appreciate the efforts to meet with them face-to-face.
Finding study abroad scholarships can be challenging, but with the help of professionals, it becomes easier. So, why not take advantage of the resources available and increase the chances of securing a scholarship or grant for the study abroad journey? Start by scheduling an appointment or dropping by these offices to ask about options!

Step 2 -  Explore and Research

One of the essential steps in getting financial aid for studying abroad is to do research. The more scholarships and grants a student applies for, the more likely he/she will receive financial assistance.

In addition, other resources like NAFSA:  Association of International Educators compile lists of scholarships for study abroad students. These can include location-specific grants and scholarships, program-specific study abroad scholarships, subject-specific grants, student-specific scholarships, university-provided study abroad scholarships, organization-provided scholarships, and government-funded scholarships.

Make sure to research thoroughly and consider all possible options. Remember that some scholarships may have specific eligibility requirements, so read the instructions carefully to ensure a student meets the criteria. Also, start the search early to give enough time to prepare robust applications.
List of Scholarships Students can Apply For:

Step 3 -  Contact the Organisation/Entity Offering Scholarships/Grants

Students should always be well-informed about the scholarship plans to apply to study abroad and stay updated on any changes or new requirements. Never hesitate to contact the funder directly. They are the experts on how to get a scholarship to study abroad, so taking the time to contact them is worth it. Doing so will demonstrate the students' proactive approach and strong interest in the scholarship, which can only work in their favour. Moreover, reaching out to the scholarship or grant funder can allow students to ask questions and receive personalized guidance on improving their application.

Step 4 -  It’s Time to Improve Your Resume

Preparing a robust application is crucial when applying for study abroad scholarships. A solid resume is a great way to showcase skills, experiences, and achievements. Always highlight any international experience, such as volunteering or interning abroad. Additionally, update all the recent campus activities and keep them concise. Keep your resume to one page.

-Work on the Cover Letter:

Cover letters are often required for study abroad scholarships, allowing students to explain why they are the best candidate for the scholarship. Avoid sending a generic cover letter and tailor it to the specific scholarship. Focus on how the study abroad experience will benefit the future goals. Always research how the specific country typically organizes their resumes and cover letters. Always write the resume in the language of the country you will be studying in.

-Letter of Recommendation:

In addition to resumes and cover letters, it is also essential to have strong letters of recommendation. These letters can come from professors, advisors, or employers who can attest to students' academic achievements, leadership skills, and character. Be sure to ask for these letters well in advance and provide recommenders with all the necessary information and materials to write a strong letter.
Finally, remember to proofread the study abroad scholarship application materials thoroughly! Spelling and grammatical errors can hurt your chances of being awarded a scholarship. Ask someone else to review all the materials, as a fresh set of eyes can catch errors you may have missed.

Step 5 - Good Recommendations Matter

Here are some tips to help students with getting strong personal references in their study abroad scholarship applications:
1.Make a list of Professors or Employers: Make a list of professors or academic advisors, internship supervisors, volunteer coordinators, or managers from part-time jobs who can write in detail about the skills and achievements of a student for the study abroad scholarships.
2.Ask for References in Advance: Give the potential references ample time to prepare and write a strong recommendation. Always email them at least a month before the application deadline and politely request if they would be willing to write a reference letter.
3.Explain the Purpose of the Application: It is essential to explain the scholarship a student is applying for and why he/she is a good candidate. This will give the reference a better idea of how to tailor their recommendation.
4.Provide Necessary Details: Make sure to provide all the necessary details for the reference, such as the application deadline, the scholarship criteria, and how to submit the reference letter. Including a copy of the resume or personal statement is an excellent idea to help them write a stronger recommendation.
5.Choose the Right Person for the Scholarship: Always select someone relevant to the scholarship applying for. For example, if a student is applying for a scholarship in environmental studies, reach out to a professor related to the same.
6.Follow-Up and Express Gratitude: After the reference has submitted their recommendation, send a follow-up email thanking them for their time and effort. Gratitude goes a long way in building relationships.

Step 6 - Stay Organised

When applying for multiple scholarships and grants, along with the study abroad program, keeping track of all the deadlines and requirements can be challenging. Creating a calendar specifically for study abroad scholarship applications is essential.

Staying organised and keeping a physical calendar or an online tool like Google Calendar helps. Keep track of all the scholarship deadlines, including any additional application materials. Set reminders for each deadline to help students stay on track.

Taking time with the application process is essential when applying for study abroad scholarships.

One of the most important things is to read and follow each scholarship's directions carefully. It will ensure that students provide all the required information and complete the application correctly. Additionally, giving enough time to complete all the applications will prevent students from feeling overburdened.

Students will increase their chances of receiving more financial aid by taking time and submitting high-quality applications.

Step 7 - Apply

Firstly, apply for study abroad scholarships as soon and thoroughly as possible. However, it may seem daunting, but every step counts and can make a student's experience more affordable and less stressful.

Take the time to read through the requirements and submit all necessary materials carefully.Customizing the applications is also crucial to increase the chances of being selected. Avoid copying and pasting from one application to another. Instead, research and tailor the study abroad scholarship application. This will show that a student is genuinely interested in their foundation and will make their application stand out.

Step 8 - Follow-Up with the Scholarship Providers:

Following up with the applied study abroad scholarships is crucial. Keeping track of the application process and the response is a necessary part of the whole process. Always be professional and courteous while following up with the study abroad scholarship providers. Start by sending a thank-you note or email to express appreciation for their consideration of the application. If a student has yet to hear back from them within the expected timeframe, politely inquire about the status of the concerned application and whether any additional information is needed. Remember that scholarship providers may receive many applications, so it is essential to be patient and respectful.

Step 9 - Get Good Grades

When securing a studying abroad scholarship, having good grades can be a significant factor in a student's success. While not all scholarships or grants require stellar grades or grade point averages, many do. Why? Because scholarship providers want to ensure that the students they support are committed to their study abroad experience and will take their academic pursuits seriously.

Scholarship providers want to invest in motivated and hard-working students. By earning good grades and demonstrating a solid academic record, students can show scholarship providers that they are serious about making the most of their study abroad experience and are worthwhile for their funding.

Step 10 - A Personal Essay

When applying for study abroad scholarships, a personal essay is one crucial component of the application. It can be daunting, but it is also an opportunity to showcase students' passion for studying abroad and the country they will visit.

Ensuring the essay is well-written, organized, and error-free is also essential. Take the time to proofread and edit the same, and consider asking a trusted friend or family member to review it. Remember that the essay is a chance to make a strong impression on the study abroad scholarship providers, so it is worth putting in the effort to make it the best it can be.

In addition to the personal essay, study abroad scholarships may require letters of recommendation, transcripts, and other supporting materials. Be sure to read the application instructions carefully, follow them closely, and submit all required materials by the deadline.

A Study Abroad Scholarship Matters

Deciding to study abroad is a dream for many students, but it can also come with a financial burden. Thus, study abroad scholarships are a vital tool for students looking to make their international education aspirations a reality.

Students can gain a global perspective and enhance their academic and personal growth by studying abroad. It is a valuable experience that can boost a student's resume to make them stand firm and fly higher.

Our hand-picked team is here to assist students in navigating the scholarship application process and finding the best opportunities to fund their study abroad journey. With our diverse experience and academic partnerships abroad, we can provide valuable insights and support to help students achieve their study abroad goals. Contact us today to learn how we can help make students' dreams of studying abroad a reality.

FAQ

Why should a student apply for a study abroad scholarship?

Study Abroad Scholarship is an aid for many aspirants who desire to study abroad. It helps to financial stress away for those who cannot afford to study abroad.

Do study abroad scholarships really help to keep financial stress at bay?

Yes, the study abroad scholarships are government funded and are a way to motivate students to fulfill their dreams. These scholarships provide incentives and cover various costs of studying abroad.

Are resumes a mandatory part of applying for study abroad scholarships?

Yes, the resumes are a crucial part of the process while applying for study abroad scholarships. The resumes are enough for the universities to understand the student and their requirements.

Can a student apply for more than one scholarship at once?

Yes,  a student can apply for more than one scholarship at once.

Do all the applicants get scholarships?

No, only the selected applicants get the study abroad scholarships.

How can a student apply for the study abroad scholarship?

The foremost task is to decide which university/college a student aspires to study in, and then research the scholarships offered by the country/university/state. The next step is to apply for the scholarships that a student fits into and follow the procedure.

What if the study abroad scholarship application is declined?

If a student’s study abroad scholarship application is declined, it is essential to contact the scholarship providers and find out what went wrong with the application. Wait for the next application process year and apply again, considering the mistakes committed earlier.
